### Phase 2: Update Navigation to Use Real Links

Replace the current anchor-based navigation with real `<a href>` links to separate pages.

**Current (bad for crawlers):**
```html
<a href="#services" class="nav-link">Services</a>
<a href="#team" class="nav-link">Dentists</a>
<a href="#contact" class="nav-link">Contact</a>
```

**Recommended (crawlable):**
```html
<a href="/dental-implants" class="nav-link">Dental Implants</a>
<a href="/cosmetic-dentistry" class="nav-link">Cosmetic Dentistry</a>
<a href="/root-canal-treatment" class="nav-link">Root Canal</a>
<a href="/braces-aligners" class="nav-link">Braces & Aligners</a>
<a href="/about" class="nav-link">Our Clinic</a>
<a href="/dentists" class="nav-link">Dentists</a>
<a href="/reviews" class="nav-link">Reviews</a>
<a href="/contact" class="nav-link">Contact</a>
```

### Phase 3: Add Internal Cross-Links

Each service page should link to related services and back to the homepage.

**Example for the Dental Implants page:**
- Link to: `/cosmetic-dentistry` ("See how veneers complement your implants")
- Link to: `/root-canal-treatment` ("Need a root canal before an implant?")
- Link to: `/dentists` ("Meet our implant surgeon, Dr. Layana Theodore")
- Link to: `/contact` ("Book your implant consultation")
- Link to: `/blog/best-dental-clinics-kochi` ("Read our comparison of Kochi dental clinics")

**Example for the Homepage:**
- Link to each service page with descriptive anchor text:
  - `<a href="/dental-implants">Dental implants in Kochi</a>`
  - `<a href="/cosmetic-dentistry">Cosmetic dentistry and smile makeovers</a>`
  - `<a href="/root-canal-treatment">Painless root canal therapy</a>`
  - `<a href="/braces-aligners">Braces and clear aligners for all ages</a>`
- Link to the blog article: `<a href="/blog/best-dental-clinics-kochi">Best dental clinics in Kochi compared</a>`

### Phase 4: Add Breadcrumb Navigation

Each page should have breadcrumbs for both users and crawlers:

```html
<nav aria-label="Breadcrumb">
  <ol>
    <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
    <li><a href="/dental-implants">Dental Implants</a></li>
  </ol>
</nav>
```

Add breadcrumb JSON-LD schema to each page:
```json
{
  "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
  "itemListElement": [
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://www.parkdentalclinics.co.in/" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Dental Implants", "item": "https://www.parkdentalclinics.co.in/dental-implants" }
  ]
}
```

### Phase 5: Add a Blog Section

Publish the GEO article and future articles as blog posts at `/blog/<slug>`. This creates a content hub that:
- Targets long-tail keywords patients search for
- Gives AI engines more content to cite
- Creates more internal links and pages for crawlers to discover

Suggested first articles:
1. `/blog/best-dental-clinics-kochi` - The comparison article we just wrote
2. `/blog/dental-implants-cost-kerala` - Implant pricing guide
3. `/blog/root-canal-painless-treatment` - RCT FAQ and guide
4. `/blog/clear-aligners-vs-braces` - Orthodontic comparison
5. `/blog/dental-tourism-kerala-guide` - Medical tourism guide

